OL,3,CMum forced to give up career as school
OL,4,Chas no room for her autistic daughter
OL,6,F"It feels like a full-time job for me.
OL,7,FSince finishing teaching, I'm working
OL,8,Fharder now advocating for her,
OL,9,Fsupporting her and trying to get what
OL,10,Fshe deserves, which is the bare
OL,11,Fminimum.
OL,13,F"It's children's right to have an
OL,14,Feducation. Why shouldn't she have what
OL,15,Fevery other child has?"
OL,17,FWhile Millie should be starting full-
OL,18,Ftime school in September, the family
OL,19,Fhave no idea when their long wait may
OL,20,Fcome to an end.
